In modeling of the infectious diseases, the incidence function play a key role as it can determine the rise and fall of epidemics and represents the number of new cases per unit time. Some factors, such as density and lifestyle of the population could affect the incidence rate openly or circuitously. Many forms of incidence rates are possible. In the conventional epidemic disease models, bilinear incidence rate \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
